Overview

FareCalc is a Python-based backend script designed for a ride-sharing system called CityCab. It calculates the estimated ride fare based on:
Distance traveled (in km)
Type of vehicle selected
Time of booking (for surge pricing)

Features:
Dynamic fare calculation
Surge pricing during peak hours (5 PM – 8 PM)
Dictionary-based rate mapping for efficiency
Error handling for invalid inputs
Clean and formatted price receipt output
